### Form Component Template
```typescript
// Template: Form Component
interface {{FormName}}Props {
  onSubmit: (data: {{DataType}}) => Promise<void>;
  initialData?: Partial<{{DataType}}>;
  loading?: boolean;
}

const {{FormName}}: React.FC<{{FormName}}Props> = ({
  onSubmit,
  initialData,
  loading = false,
}) => {
  const form = useForm<{{DataType}}>({
    defaultValues: initialData,
    resolver: zodResolver({{validationSchema}}),
  });

  const handleSubmit = async (data: {{DataType}}) => {
    try {
      await onSubmit(data);
      form.reset();
    } catch (error) {
      // Handle error
    }
  };

  return (
    <Form {...form}>
      <form onSubmit={form.handleSubmit(handleSubmit)} className="space-y-4">
        {/* Form fields */}
        <Button type="submit" loading={loading}>
          Submit
        </Button>
      </form>
    </Form>
  );
};
```

## Cursor Composer Workflows

### 1. Feature Development Workflow
```
1. ANALYZE: "Analyze the requirements for [FEATURE] in our guitar marketplace"
2. PLAN: "Create a development plan for implementing [FEATURE] with our tech stack"
3. IMPLEMENT: "Generate the necessary components, hooks, and database changes"
4. TEST: "Create unit tests and integration tests for [FEATURE]"
5. DOCUMENT: "Update documentation and add JSDoc comments"
```

### 2. Bug Fix Workflow
```
1. REPRODUCE: "Help me reproduce and understand this bug: [BUG_DESCRIPTION]"
2. ANALYZE: "Analyze the root cause considering our architecture and data flow"
3. FIX: "Implement a fix following our established patterns and security requirements"
4. TEST: "Create tests to prevent regression of this issue"
5. VERIFY: "Review the fix for potential side effects or security implications"
```

### 3. Refactoring Workflow
```
1. ASSESS: "Analyze this code for improvement opportunities: [CODE_BLOCK]"
2. PLAN: "Suggest refactoring approach maintaining backward compatibility"
3. REFACTOR: "Implement the refactoring with proper TypeScript types"
4. VALIDATE: "Ensure all existing functionality remains intact"
5. OPTIMIZE: "Identify any performance improvements possible"
```

